executeQuery

@IPSJexlMethod(description="executes a JCR Query",
               params={@IPSJexlParam(name="query",description="the query string"),@IPSJexlParam(name="maxRows",description="max number of rows to return"),@IPSJexlParam(name="params",description="parameters for query"),@IPSJexlParam(name="locale",description="locale for collating results")})
public java.util.List<java.util.Map<java.lang.String,javax.jcr.Value>> executeQuery(java.lang.String query,
                                                                                                                                                      int maxRows,
                                                                                                                                                      java.util.Map<java.lang.String,? extends java.lang.Object> params,
                                                                                                                                                      java.lang.String locale)
                                                                             throws javax.jcr.query.InvalidQueryException,
                                                                                    javax.jcr.RepositoryException
Executes a JCR Query. The results are returned as a List. Each element of the list is a Map that contains name / value pairs representing the columns of the query.

Parameters:
query - the JCR Query to execute
maxRows - the maximum number of rows. Set to -1 for unlimited rows.
params - the parameters to pass to the query.
locale - the locale used for sorting results.
Returns:
a list of result rows. Each Row is a map of name and value pairs. never null but may be empty.
Throws:
javax.jcr.query.InvalidQueryException
javax.jcr.RepositoryException

executeQueryNodes

@IPSJexlMethod(description="executes a JCR Query and returns the Nodes",
               params={@IPSJexlParam(name="query",description="the query string"),@IPSJexlParam(name="maxRows",description="max number of rows to return"),@IPSJexlParam(name="params",description="parameters for query"),@IPSJexlParam(name="locale",description="locale for collating results")})
public javax.jcr.NodeIterator executeQueryNodes(java.lang.String query,
                                                                                                                  int maxRows,
                                                                                                                  java.util.Map<java.lang.String,? extends java.lang.Object> params,
                                                                                                                  java.lang.String locale)
                                         throws javax.jcr.query.InvalidQueryException,
                                                javax.jcr.RepositoryException
Executes a JCR Query and returns the Nodes. The resulting NodeIterator can be used to load the individual Nodes rather than using the result values.

Parameters:
query - the JCR Query
maxRows - the maximum number of rows. Set to -1 for unlimited rows.
params - the the parameters to pass to the query.
locale - the locale. Defaults to the JVM system locale if not present.
Returns:
the Nodes from the query. Never null but may be empty.
Throws:
javax.jcr.query.InvalidQueryException
javax.jcr.RepositoryException
